# Village Health Monitoring System — Flutter Updates Walkthrough

## What Was Accomplished
The Flutter mobile application has been thoroughly reviewed and updated to connect seamlessly with the deployed production backend (`https://village-health-backend.onrender.com`). Critical features regarding security, API request reliability, token interpolation, and application workflows were addressed.

### 1. Updated API Service ([lib/services/api_service.dart](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/frontend/lib/services/api_service.dart))
- Fixed incorrect string interpolation (`'Bearer $token'` instead of `Bearer $token`).
- Implemented global **10-second timeouts** on all API calls: `.timeout(const Duration(seconds: 10))`.
- Added standard headers across all payload-dependent files (`Content-Type: application/json` and `Authorization`).
- Added robust logging using `debugPrint` (which avoids polluting production logs) to track `API REQ`, `API RES`, and `API ERR`.
- Created an [UnauthorizedException](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/frontend/lib/services/api_service.dart#8-14) intercept for detecting `401 Unauthorized` responses and signaling the frontend to drop the session and log out the user.
- Configured real API usage for Visit Verification (`POST /api/visit/verify`) instead of attempting to blindly verify the user’s coordinates solely on the local device.

### 2. Base Configuration Updates
- Modified [lib/utils/constants.dart](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/frontend/lib/utils/constants.dart) to use `AppConstants.baseUrl = 'https://village-health-backend.onrender.com/api'`.
- Kept [AuthService](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/frontend/lib/services/auth_service.dart#3-34) untouched since it **already correctly utilises** `flutter_secure_storage` exclusively for reading/writing sensitive tokens as requested.
- Created [distance_calculator.dart](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/frontend/lib/utils/distance_calculator.dart) to adhere precisely to the requested directory structure, porting over Haversine distance tracking functionality logic.

### 3. Screen Improvements (UI handling of API behaviour)
- **Map Screen ([map_screen.dart](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/frontend/lib/screens/map_screen.dart))**: Included handlers to purge secure tokens via [AuthService](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/frontend/lib/services/auth_service.dart#3-34) and transition the navigator back to the [LoginScreen](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/frontend/lib/screens/login_screen.dart#6-12) aggressively if an [UnauthorizedException](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/frontend/lib/services/api_service.dart#8-14) gets emitted.
- **Visit Verification Screen ([visit_verification_screen.dart](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/frontend/lib/screens/visit_verification_screen.dart))**: Overhauled location verification to actually transmit `latitude` and `longitude` fields to the API via [verifyVisit](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/backend/controllers/visitController.js#21-56). Handles timeouts and server errors dynamically alongside existing [Unauthorized](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/frontend/lib/services/api_service.dart#130-135) session protection. 
- **Patient Form ([patient_form_screen.dart](file:///c:/Users/jdbha/Downloads/village-health-system/frontend/lib/screens/patient_form_screen.dart))**: Inputs explicitly stripped or sanitized via `.trim()`. Enhanced duplicate-submission prevention with robust UI-blocking boolean flags (`_isSubmitting`).

